  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(16) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "But now . . . .",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—How different is the case with you, cries St. James; you actually glory and delight in your own self-confidence and presumption, and every such rejoicing is evil. The word for “boastings” is the same as that translated “the pride of life” in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1John 2:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "i.e., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "its braggart boastfulness, not the innocent gladness of living. It is the trust of the “ungodly” (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 10:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “There shall no harm happen unto me”), and the mistaken confidence of even such godly men as Job (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Job 29:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “shall die in my nest”), before the Almighty instructs them by trouble, and loss, and pain.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
