        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "But now.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " As is actually the case, \"ye glory in your vauntings.\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἈλαζονείΑ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ":  only here and in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 John 2:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; in the LXX., in 2 Macc. 9:8 and Wisd. 5:8. It is a favorite word with St. Clement of Rome. On its meaning and distinction from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ὑπερηφανία",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and other kindred words, see Trench on ' Synonyms,' p. 95; and cf. Westcott on the 'Epistles of St. John,' p. 64. The vice of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἀλάζων",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " \"centers in self and is consummated in his absolute self-exaltation, while the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ὑπερήφανος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " shows his character by his overweening treatment of others. The ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἀλάζων",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " sins most against truth; the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ὑπερήφανος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " sins most against love.\" This extract will serve to show the fitness of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἀλαζονεία",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " rather than ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ὑπερηφανία",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " in the passage before us. The verse should be rendered, as in R.V., \"But now ye glory (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "καυχᾶσθε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") in your vauntings: all such glorying (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "καύχησις",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") is evil.\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "Καύχησις",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is the act, not the matter (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "καύχημα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), of glorying. James 4:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
